<seg id=1> China Planing to Fill In Millions of Hectares of Sealand For Settlement of 20-30 Million Residents Next Century </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (FNA news from Beijing)The English newspaper"China Daily" reported yesterday that China was planning to accomodate 20 to 30 million of population in the coastal areas  next century through filling in the sea. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Experts attending the fill-in-the-sea meeting in Xiaoshan Zhejiang revealed that the governmnet hopes to fill in 1 million hectare of sea within 40 to 50 years along the 18,000 km long coastal line. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> "China Daily" said that about 20 to 30 million people will live in that area. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> This newspaper quoted Professor Yu Zhiyin,"from the angle of techniques, the problem is not the possibility of filling in sea but the lack of capital. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Resources indicated that despite of the coming enviroment problems,"it would still be the best way to resolve the shortage of land resources in the next century especially good to China with so large a population. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The plan would also promote new rising trades and provide more employment opportunities as well. </seg>
<seg id=8> China plans to invest the infrastructure in order to avoid impact of Asian financial crisis. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> Deputy Secretary General of the meetiong Zuo Zongmo said,"This is more than agriculture. Those lands could be of multi-uses such forestry ,industry and tourism. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> Although China adheres to One-Child policy, its population is expected to keep on growing and to reach a top of 1.6 billion till the mid of next century. </seg>
<seg id=11> The present population of China is 1.23 billion. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> And more than 90% of the population are living on only one third of the territory. </seg>
</p>
